Senegal Energy Shortages Cost $430 Million a Year, Le Pop Says

-- B y   D r e w   H i n s h a w
-- 
2011-04-05T13:04:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/senegal-energy-shortages-cost-430-million-a-year-le-pop-says.html
Power outages and fuel shortages in
 Senegal  cost the West African country 200 billion West African
CFA francs ($430 million) a year, Le Pop reported, citing Karim Wade, the energy minister.  The number of customers at Senelec, the state-owned
electricity company, increased to 880,000 customers in 2010 from
200,000 in 2000, the Dakar-based newspaper cited Wade as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Drew Hinshaw in Johannesburg at 
 dhinshaw@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  